{"ts": "2026-06-12T03:20:21.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "L2 task decomposition", "agent": "planner-l2", "tokens_in": 512, "tokens_out": 4512, "elapsed_ms": 83740, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level 2 Planner. Decompose the user task into subtasks.\n\nOutput JSON:\n{{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {{\"task_id\": \"short-name\", \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\"}}\n  ]\n}}\n\nRules:\n- Each subtask should be a focused, self-contained unit of work\n- Include file names and output expectations in descriptions\n- For simple tasks, 2-3 subtasks; for complex tasks, 4-6\n- FRONTEND: Always include an index.html (main entry page). Additional pages\n  (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine, but index.html must exist and link to them.\n  Subtask descriptions should specify what content/sections each file contains.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences\n\n## Specialty\nfrontend\n\n## User Request\nBuild a creative agency portfolio website for a fictional design studio called 'Prisma Creative'. Deliver as index.html, styles.css, and app.js.\n\nRequirements:\n- Hero section with a bold animated text typing effect (typewriter animation using JavaScript setInterval or CSS steps)\n- Project showcase: masonry-style grid (use CSS grid with varying row spans) of 6 portfolio items — each has a gradient overlay on hover that reveals project name and category\n- Services section: 4 service cards (Branding, Web Design, Motion, Strategy) each with an SVG-like icon (use emoji or CSS shapes). Cards should have a subtle border animation on hover (pseudo-element sweep)\n- Client logos strip: horizontal scrolling row of logo placeholders with CSS grayscale filter that removes on hover\n- Team section: 4 team member cards with circular photo placeholder, name, role, and short bio. Cards tilt slightly on hover (CSS transform: rotateY)\n- Contact form: name, email, project type dropdown, message textarea — validate on submit, show error messages below each field, success confirmation with smooth fade-in\n- Sticky navbar that shrinks on scroll (smaller height, smaller logo)\n- Fully responsive with mobile-first approach", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T03:22:22.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Agent Creator L2 — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-l2", "tokens_in": 1514, "tokens_out": 6663, "elapsed_ms": 121052, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Agent Creator (Level 2 — Template-Based). Your role: create worker agent configurations by selecting from predefined templates.\n\n## Available Templates for this Specialty\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"role\": \"ux_designer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a UX/UI Content Designer. Generate real content, copy, and image prompts for the web page. Save as content_brief.json.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": []\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"role\": \"html_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are an HTML Developer. Write semantic HTML5. Save as index.html. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"role\": \"css_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a CSS Developer. Write modern CSS with variables, flexbox, grid. Save as styles.css. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/css_styling.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"role\": \"js_developer\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a JavaScript Developer. Write vanilla ES6+ JS. Save as app.js. Use write_file ONLY.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"frontend/accessibility.json\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"role\": \"frontend_tester\",\n    \"system_prompt\": \"You are a Frontend Tester. Validate HTML, CSS, JS files. Write test_report.json with structured issues.\",\n    \"default_tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ],\n    \"skill_paths\": [\n      \"tester/e2e_testing.json\"\n    ]\n  }\n]\n\n## Available Tools\nThe tool menu for this specialty:\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Task Plan\nThe planner has decomposed the task into subtasks:\n{\n  \"subtasks\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"html-structure\",\n      \"description\": \"Create index.html with the overall page structure: header with logo and nav links, main content with sections (hero, projects, services, clients, team, contact), and footer. Use semantic HTML5 elements. Link to styles.css and app.js. Use placeholder text and data attributes where needed.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"hero-section\",\n      \"description\": \"Implement the hero section in index.html and styles.css: a large bold heading (with id for typewriter target). Write the typewriter animation JavaScript in app.js that types out the heading text letter by letter using setInterval. Ensure the hero is visually impactful.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"project-showcase\",\n      \"description\": \"Add the project showcase section to index.html: a masonry-style CSS grid with 6 items. Each item has a background image placeholder, and on hover shows a gradient overlay with project name and category. Write the corresponding CSS in styles.css with varying grid-row spans to achieve the masonry effect.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"services-clients\",\n      \"description\": \"Add the services section (4 cards with emoji icons and pseudo-element border animation on hover) and the client logos strip (horizontal scrolling, grayscale filter) to index.html. Style them in styles.css, ensuring the card border sweep uses a ::before or ::after pseudo-element.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"team-contact\",\n      \"description\": \"Add the team section (4 team cards with circular photo placeholder, name, role, bio; rotateY tilt on hover) and the contact form (name, email, project type dropdown, message textarea) to index.html. Style in styles.css. Implement form validation in app.js: on submit, validate fields, show error messages below each field, and on success show a confirmation message with fade-in.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"navbar-responsive\",\n      \"description\": \"Implement the sticky navbar that shrinks on scroll: add JavaScript in app.js to toggle a CSS class based on scroll position; write CSS for the smaller state. Also, ensure the entire website is fully responsive with a mobile-first approach, adding necessary media queries to styles.css for all sections.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Your Job\nFor EACH subtask in the plan:\n1. Pick the BEST matching template from the available templates above\n2. Optionally EDIT the system_prompt to add task-specific details (file names, specific requirements)\n3. Select a SUBSET of tools from the available tool menu that the worker needs\n4. Set skill_paths from the template\n\n## Rules\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences, no extra text\n- worker_name MUST match a template name (or be \"tester\")\n- system_prompt: start from the template prompt, then add task-specific instructions\n- tool_names: only pick from the available tool menu\n- skill_paths: copy the template's skill_paths or leave empty\n- FRONTEND FILE NAMES: The html worker always outputs index.html (the main page).\n  The css worker always outputs styles.css. The js worker always outputs app.js.\n  Additional HTML pages (hero.html, about.html, etc.) are fine but index.html\n  is the canonical main entry. Add section-specific instructions to the prompt,\n  do NOT rename the output file.\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"template_name\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full customized system instructions for the worker\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\"],\n      \"skill_paths\": [\"path/to/skill.json\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "meta": {}}
